    • Method Detail

      • retrieveTransactionMetaData

        @Deprecated
void retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters transactionMetaDataParameters)
        Deprecated. since 6.5.0.1.a
        Retrieves meta-data information related to a transaction. The information required to submit along with the transactionMetaDataParameters parameter will vary according to the processing rules. For example during a "discovery" processing rule, the TransactionMetaDataParameters would require to provide the checkoutToken value. Some of the calls to retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) might require providing the TransactionMetaDataParameters.setExecutingFlowRule(com.paydiant.android.core.enums.transactionflow.TransactionFlowRule). This method provides the provides the polling implementations for eligible flow rules. (i.e.; Flow rules with TransactionFlowRuleSpecification.isExecuteRuleAndPollForResult() value is set to true).
        Parameters:
        transactionMetaDataParameters - transaction meta data parameters containing checkout token value, paydiant reference id, receipt/offer search parameters along with the current execution rule. These parameter properties would be mandatory or optional depending on the next execution rule.

      • retrieveTransactionMetaDataWithoutPolling

        void retrieveTransactionMetaDataWithoutPolling(TransactionMetaDataParameters transactionMetaDataParameters)
        Retrieves meta-data information related to a transaction. The information required to submit along with the transactionMetaDataParameters parameter will vary according to the processing rules. For example during a "discovery" processing rule, the TransactionMetaDataParameters would require to provide the checkoutToken value. Some of the calls to retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) might require providing the TransactionMetaDataParameters.setExecutingFlowRule(com.paydiant.android.core.enums.transactionflow.TransactionFlowRule). This method does not perform polling like the retrieveTransactionMetaData(TransactionMetaDataParameters) method, and app developers are required to implement the necessary polling mechanisms for eligible flow rules.
        Parameters:
        transactionMetaDataParameters - transaction meta data parameters containing checkout token value, paydiant reference id, receipt/offer search parameters along with the current execution rule. These parameter properties would be mandatory or optional depending on the next execution rule.
        Since:
        6.5.0.1.a

      • updateTransaction

        void updateTransaction(TransactionParameters transactionParameters)
        Updates the current transaction with the required offer information, payment tender information, tip amounts, cash back/cash access information, transaction confirmation etc.. The information provided will vary according to the processing rules. (E.g.: "submit offers" processing rule will require any selected offers for a given transaction and "submit offers and payment tenders" rule would need to provide both selected offers and the payment instrument.
        Parameters:
        transactionParameters - the transaction parameters containing offers, payment tender information, tip amounts, cash back/cash access information, transaction confirmation etc.. required for the next processing rule.
